					<p class="title">Lead Engineer – Computational Fluid Dynamics</p>
					<p>
						Sewis Van Zyl is responsible, amongst others, for general building performance modelling at Greenbuild Consultants. With almost 10 years of experience in Computational Fluid Dynamics (CFD), he has a deep passion for combining the art and science of developing effective CFD solutions for complex natural ventilation and wind flow problems. Sewis holds a Ph.D. in Mechanical Engineering from the University of Stellenbosch. Prior to Greenbuild Consultants, Sewis did post-doctoral work at both the University of Stellenbosch and National Renewable Energy Laboratory in the USA.
					</p>
				</div>
